-- Toyota sees '08 U.S. industry sales at low-15 mln units
-- 
-- Thu May 1, 2008 4:11pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/01/us-toyota-outlook-idUSN0135351420080501

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Toyota Motor Co ( 7203.T ) 

 * Toyota sees U.S. industry-wide auto sales for 2008 in low-15 million unit range. * Toyota estimates U.S. auto sales for April near the annualized rate of 14.6 million to 14.7 million units. *Toyota says inventory of its Tundra full-size pickup truck is near 80 days of supply, is offering incentives to reduce stock. (Reporting by  Soyoung Kim )